title: The 25th-ranked University of Mobile men's soccer team remained unbeaten in SSAC action Thursday | AL.com
text:
The 25 th -ranked University of Mobile men's soccer team remained unbeaten in Southern States Athletic Conference action with a 3-2 road win at Middle Georgia Thursday evening thanks to three early second-half goals. Hayden Dees picked up his first-career victory in goal for the Rams.
Trailing 1-0 after the opening 45 minutes, the Rams scored all three of their goals within the first 10 minutes of the final period. Matthew McArthur tied the game when he went top shelf after a cross from Newton Henry in the 47 th minute, and Henry later added the eventual game-winner with an unassisted goal in the 53 rd minute.
Scoring Summary
44:16 – Middle Georgia – Rasmus Arousell (assist by Daniel Ward)
47:47 – Mobile – Matthew McArthur (assist by Newton Henry)
52:19 – Mobile – John Plumbar (assist by Matthew McArthur)
53:51 – Mobile – Newton Henry (unassisted)
70:09 – Middle Georgia – Jon Gisli Strom (assist by Mattias Rosell)
Numbers Game
3 – Mobile has a three-game winning streak and five-game unbeaten streak going
7 – Mobile put seven of 13 shots on target
12 – Middle Georgia put 12 of 17 shots on frame
27 – There were 27 combined fouls and five cards in a physical contest
Additional Notes
Dees made a career-high eight stops in the game Mobile has taken 10+ shots in nine games on the year with a high of 20 v. Louisiana College After having no points through his first 13 games played, McArthur has three points in each of the last two contests with one goal and four assists Newton Henry leads Mobile with nine goals and 22 points Next
Mobile (9-4-2, 3-0-2) visits Brewton-Parker Saturday at 3 p.m. for an SSAC contest.
